Definition: You will be shown text describing {Biological Summary} along with a domain. Your job is to determine if the shown domain is {Relationship Summary} that the text describes. {Task-Specific Relationship}You may only output yes or no. If the domain shown is the one described, you should respond yes. Otherwise, you should respond no.
Biological Summary: a biological process accomplished by multiple molecular activities where proteins are involved
Task-Specific Relationship: When a domain family appears in a set of functionally similar proteins, the conserved process described at the most specific level to be relevant to all proteins in that family are associated with the domain family, and thus all domains belonging to the family.
